HB Draft 2026 Regular Session
Abstract: Provides relative to fireworks.
Present law provides for definitions.
Proposed law amends definitions of "proximate display", "public display", "pyrotechnic
operator", and "pyrotechnic special effects operator" and repeals definitions of "Class C
public display" and "pyrotechnic operator".
Present law prohibits certain types of fireworks from being possessed, used, or sold in this
state.
Proposed law provides that only items classified as 1.4G fireworks in compliance with
American Pyrotechnics Association (APA) Standard 87-1A may be sold by a properly
licensed retailer to the public.
Present law authorizes permissible items of fireworks to be sold at retail only from noon on
June 16th through midnight on July 5th and noon on December 15th through midnight on
January 1st of each calendar year.
